sql : structured query language 
it is used to store data in a database by converting the data into tables.
the main operations that can be done in a sql are : create read update delete
the 4 main branches of the sql are : DDL (data defination language) 
                                     DML (data manipulation language)
                                     DCL (data control language)
                                     TCL (transaction control language)
                                     
